This is a followup of mockito issues https://github.com/mockito/mockito/issues/233 and PR https://github.com/mockito/mockito/issues/234

The fix 6f223d93ee57b199abf0e7abaf4837df6d041f41 here don't handle _compilation_, so bytecode is can be generated, but cannot be instantiated (`IllegalAccessError`).

The issue is probably there `MethodRegistry.Default.Compiled#getInstrumentedMethods` does not check if methods are visible, like other components of 6f223d93ee57b199abf0e7abaf4837df6d041f41.

I'm guessing that the implementation should be something like : 

``` java
@Override
public MethodList getInstrumentedMethods() {
    return new MethodList.Explicit(new ArrayList<MethodDescription>(implementations.keySet())).filter(not(isTypeInitializer()).and(isVisibleTo(instrumentedType)));
}
```
